    <subfield code="o">24</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">More precisely, the coupling between the two wells (due to the weak 'quantum tunneling' through the high potential barrier) introduces a correction term of order exp[- th + 1 th- 2 dth U(th)] to the r.h.s of the WKB quantization condition (11) [18, 23]. This term is of the order of e- [?] [?]U [?] e-c - 0 [see Eq. (9)] and is therefore negligible in the c - [?] limit [18, 23]</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
